    "dialogue": [
        {
            "text": "I'm Sonya. I suppose I'm just your average mage-for-hire now. This place seems interesting enough. I suppose I'll stick around and see what sort of trouble I can get into.",
            "context": "joined"
        },
        {
            "text": "This world's cultures are simply fascinating. If you would allow me to study them, it might aid you too.",
            "context": "castle"
        },
        {
            "text": "I used to work for a very unsavory character. And before that, well...it's really none of your business, is it?",
            "context": "castle"
        },
        {
            "text": "Is there a reason for a noncombatant to be on the battlefield? I can't help but worry for you.",
            "context": "castle"
        },
        {
            "text": "What do you say to a shopping trip? I'll pick out some new clothes for you, from head to toe—it'll be fun!",
            "context": "castle"
        },
        {
            "text": "Might be time for a manicure... My magic always feels its strongest when my hands look their best.",
            "context": "castle"
        },
        {
            "text": "I carry greetings from <Friend Name>. You two seem awfully close... I'm a little jealous.",
            "context": "friend"
        },
        {
            "text": "Hmmm... How do you like me now?",
            "context": "level"
        },
        {
            "text": "Did you expect anything less?",
            "context": "level"
        },
        {
            "text": "Brute force just isn't my style.",
            "context": "level"
        },
        {
            "text": "Ahhh, how nice... It's like I've been born anew.",
            "context": "growth"
        },
        {
            "text": "Oh, <Player Name>. Did you come to see me so I could spoil you? You're just too cute! Aw, stop squirming—I'm only kidding. I had two older sisters, and they spoiled me rotten. So can you blame me for teasing you? At least I finally understand why you join us in battle. It's because you know your presence is a boost to our morale. You really are an exceptional leader. It's actually charming, in a way... Seeing your face always puts my mind at ease. Remember to give me a smile now and then, OK?",
            "context": "maxed"
        }
    ],
